title: For Sale:  Taurus PT111 MILLENNIUM G2 9mm Polymer Grip Subcompact
location: Eden Prairie, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
Hello all - 
I'm selling my Taurus PT111 MILLENNIUM G2. It's an awesome shooter, and is shockingly accurate for it's small size. I originally bought it to conceal and carry. It's 12+1 capacity is amazing for a handgun of this size. It's great on the range and has performed flawlessly - not a single hang up. I've probably shot 400 rounds through and I've always cleaned it. The gun is new - it was manufactured in March if my memory serves me correctly.

This is an awesome gun for the price. The longer I've had it the more I've realized it's awesome features. Here are some of my favorites.
- DA/SA so you can keep either a heavy double action trigger pull (some people like this for carrying) or a crisp and light single action trigger pull (which is regarded as better for target shooting).
- Nice sights, adjustable (and replaceable if you choose).
- Has a safety switch on the frame, a trigger safety (like a Glock), and a drop-safe firing pin safety.
- Stippling on the grip is excellent.
- Takedown for cleaning is very easy.
- There is a tool which can disable the whole gun for safe storage.
- Lifetime warranty.
etc.

I've got the box and the two magazines that came with the gun and everything which came originally packaged. The gun has been carried so cosmetically there is some blueing rubbed away and some other blemishes. Functionally it's perfect.

I've attached the factory photos, but I can take some pictures of my specific one if you like.

Here are some more specs from Taurus:

With its lightweight 22 oz. polymer frame, thin profile, and ramped 3.2 inch barrel, the newly designed Millennium G2 is the ideal concealed carry handgun. Available in two compact models—PT 111 and PT 140—the Millennium G2 features an accessory rail, high-profile sights, an aggressive, textured grip and melted edges for added comfort and easy concealment.

Taurus Security System (TSS)s
Taurus family of semi-auto pistols now feature the Taurus Security System, which provides instant-ready defense with built-in ability to secure your pistol and make it inoperable at the turn of a key. When the Security System is engaged, the pistol cannot be fired or cocked and the gun's manual safety cannot be disengaged. As with our revolver Security System, the device is part of the firearm and cannot be lost, and the same special Security Key works for both the revolver and pistol Systems (two keys come with most guns). To engage: simply insert the Key into the button on the rear or side of the pistol and rotate one-quarter turn clockwise. This engages the Security System. The manual safety cannot be moved and the trigger cannot be pulled. To disengage: simply rotate the key one-quarter turn back. This releases the Security System, yet leaves the pistol's manual safety in the "safe" position until you are ready to release it yourself and fire the gun.
Loaded Chamber Indicator
Taurus provides a loaded chamber indicator on all new compact, medium and large frame pistols. As with all Taurus safety and security innovations, the indicator in no way interferes with the operation of your pistol and is provided at no extra cost, but gives you an "at-a-glance" verification that there is a round in the chamber. When a round is in the chamber, the ejector pops out of the slide, exposing a red strip just behind the ejection port. While any loaded chamber indicator is no substitute for common sense and safe firearm handling, it is one more example of Taurus' commitment to outstanding firearms.
Accessory Rail
Features the Genuine Picatinny Rail allowing use of many accessories

title: For Sale/Trade:  Eddystone Model of 1917
postcontent:
More realistic pricing.
I have a Eddystone Model of 1917, caliber .30-06.  Sometimes known as the American Enfield, this was the main battle rifle of the American Expeditionary Force that went to France to fight in WWI.  Sargent York used one when he fought in France in his famous encounter.

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alvin_C._York 
York worked his way into position to silence the German machine guns. York recalled:

And those machine guns were spitting fire and cutting down the undergrowth all around me something awful. And the Germans were yelling orders. You never heard such a racket in all of your life. I didn't have time to dodge behind a tree or dive into the brush... As soon as the machine guns opened fire on me, I began to exchange shots with them. There were over thirty of them in continuous action, and all I could do was touch the Germans off just as fast as I could. I was sharp shooting... All the time I kept yelling at them to come down. I didn't want to kill any more than I had to. But it was they or I. And I was giving them the best I had.

During the assault, six German soldiers in a trench near York charged him with fixed bayonets. York had fired all the rounds in his M1917 Enfield rifle, but drew his .45 Colt automatic pistol and shot all six soldiers before they could reach him.

This one was manufactured in 1918 and as far as I can tell is in basically original overall condition.  In other words, it has not been refurbished or rebuilt.  The finish is great with some original bluing left with the normal patina expected, no rust anywhere on the rifle.  The stock certainly looks to have been lightly sanded and varnished and is in great shape with some light cartouches still visible.  The rifling is strong, the bolt smooth and locks up perfectly, shoots excellent, no issues.  I will include a correct 1917 bayonet with the rifle (no scabbard)  I have had a lot of fun shooting it and it always attracts curiosity at the range.  I have really enjoyed letting young people shoot this piece of American Military history.  I doubt that you will ever see one like this in the store.

Now I am interested in moving on and trying other areas of my hobby. 

Sell or Trade: Cash sale $650 rifle, $150 Bayonet / offer, Trade value $800 +/- depending on what you have.  I will include some amount of .30-06 ball ammo with trade, depending.

Straight trade.  This is a C&R qualified rifle so no FFL needed to transfer, all laws apply and I will want a peek at your CO DL to prove residency, if trading I will pay my own transfer and BGC at NorCO area FFL.
